text: My Name is a 1989 album by Swedish pop singer Lena Philipsson. The album peaked at #10 at the Swedish album chart. On the album, she contributed as songwriter together with Torgny Söderberg. The entire album is in English and sold 130,000 copies within 2 months. ==Track listing== #"LoPhus" #"My Name" #"Standing In My Rain" #"Together We're Alone" #"Only You (Can Move Me Like You Do)" #"Blue Jeans" #"LooPHus" #"Why (Så lätt kommer du inte undan)" #"Strong Man" #"Taking-Care Day" #"Taboo Taboo" #"How Does It Feel" #"Leave A Light" ==Chart positions== {| class="wikitable" !align="left"|Chart (1989-1990) !align="center"|Peak position |- |align="left"|Sweden |align="center"|10 |} ==References== Category:1989 albums Category:Lena Philipsson albums
